            "creation_date": 1410501813,
            "body": "<p>You have your true/false results the wrong way around.<\/p>\n\n<p>The ternary operator is:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>(something) = (condition) ? (value if true) : (value if false);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Hence \"if current credit is greater than or equal to 120, then set cred remaining to 0\" would be done as:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>return (currentEarnedCr &gt;= 120) ? 0 : (REQUIRED_CR - currentEarnedCr);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 25801746,
            "question_id": 25801706
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f83cc994c98e417a3e0e0971c0480293?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2102673,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1869846,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1869846/ruchira-gayan-ranaweera",
                "reputation": 35683,
                "display_name": "Ruchira Gayan Ranaweera",
                "accept_rate": 56
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1410501905,
            "creation_date": 1410501905,
            "body": "<p>You have to change the order<\/p>\n\n<p>Change<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>return (currentEarnedCr &gt;= 120)?(REQUIRED_CR - currentEarnedCr):0;   \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>To<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>return (currentEarnedCr &gt;= 120)?0:(REQUIRED_CR - currentEarnedCr);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Why?<\/p>\n\n<p>In <code>Ternary Operator<\/code> <\/p>\n\n<pre><code> result = someCondition ? value1 : value2;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>if <code>someCondition<\/code> is <code>true<\/code> <code>result<\/code> become <code>value1<\/code> else <code>result<\/code> become <code>value2<\/code><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 25801767,
            "question_id": 25801706
        }
    ],
